{
  "texts": [
    "Using heuristics facilitates cognitive efficiency since people select specific sensory inputs to process, disregarding other stimuli.",
    "Therefore, the level of attention paid affects the amount of information assimilated and processed [21] to prevent an overwhelming accumulation of information which could result in cognitive overload and, consequently, failure to comprehend and assimilate the content of the messages [34].",
    "Individuals perceive audio and images as more closely mirroring the real world than text [22].",
    "Within the metacognitive experience, fluency is central to comprehending why people believe false information.",
    "As suggested in [35], fluency implies that humans are more inclined to perceive messages as valid if they are familiar with them."
  ]
}